<doc id="396007" wikidata="Q3133058" url="?curid=396007" title="Henry Sarwer-Foner">
<text>Henry Sarwer-Foner is a Canadian television director. He has won numerous Canadian Screen Awards, Gemini, DGC and Canadian Comedy Awards as the director of &quot;This Hour Has 22 Minutes&quot;, &quot;Made in Canada&quot; and &quot;Corner Gas&quot;.

In 2007 Henry Sarwer-Foner directed the CBC TV special &quot;Bob &amp; Doug McKenzie&#x27;s Two-Four Anniversary&quot;. The show featured notable guest appearances by Geddy Lee and others, with hosting by Canadian former prime minister Paul Martin.

