<doc id="396014" wikidata="Q3075294" url="?curid=396014" title="Local zeta function">
<text>In mathematics, the local zeta function (sometimes called the congruent zeta function or the Hasse–Weil zeta function) is defined as

:formula_1

where is a non-singular -dimensional projective algebraic variety over the field with elements and is the number of points of defined over the finite field extension of .

Making the variable transformation gives
