where:
* formula_48 is the momentum density, a conservation variable.
* formula_73 is the total energy density (total energy per unit volume).

Here formula_33 has length N + 2 and formula_34 has size N(N + 2). In general (not only in the Froude limit) Euler equations are expressible as:

where formula_49 is the force density, a conservation variable.

We remark that also the Euler equation even when conservative (no external field, Froude limit) have no Riemann invariants in general. Some further assumptions are required

